        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued October 21 at 6:44PM EDT by NWS Charleston WV</headline>
        <description>At 644 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 11
miles northeast of Grantsville, moving east at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Auburn, Newberne, Alum Bridge, Coxs Mills, Linn, Big Springs, Berea,
Tanner, Grove, Leopold, Troy, and Burnt House.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
